# bmad-todo-app — Cursor Rules

# Stack: FastAPI 0.115 / Python 3.11 · React 18 / TypeScript · PostgreSQL 16 · Playwright

## ARCHITECTURE

Strict layering — never skip layers.

- Backend: Router → crud.py → Session. No SQLAlchemy queries inside routers.
- Frontend: Component → Hook → api.ts. No raw fetch() outside api.ts.

## PYTHON / FASTAPI

- Pydantic v2 only: use `field_validator` + `@classmethod`, `ConfigDict(from_attributes=True)`, `model_config`. Never use `@validator`, `class Config`, or `orm_mode`.
- Timestamps: always `datetime.now(timezone.utc)`. Never `datetime.utcnow()`.
- UUID PKs: Python-side `default=uuid.uuid4`, never `server_default` (breaks SQLite test suite).
- HTTP codes are a contract: POST → 201, DELETE → 204 with explicit `Response(status_code=204)`, GET/PATCH → 200.
- Always `db.refresh(obj)` after commit before returning an ORM model.
- 404s use `raise HTTPException(status_code=404, detail="<Resource> not found")`.

## TYPESCRIPT / REACT

- Every function must declare an explicit return type. No `any` — use `unknown` + narrowing.
- `useState` must always have an explicit generic: `useState<Todo[]>([])`, never `useState([])`.
- Server-authoritative UI: after every mutation, call `fetchTodos()`. Never patch local state optimistically.
- All HTTP calls go through the typed helpers in `api.ts`. Import as `import * as api from "../api"`.

## CSS

- Use CSS custom properties defined in `frontend/src/index.css`. Never hardcode colours, radii, or shadows.
  - Colours: `--color-accent`, `--color-accent-hover`, `--color-bg`, `--color-surface`, `--color-text`, `--color-text-muted`, `--color-danger`
  - Radii: `--radius-sm`, `--radius-md`, `--radius-lg`
  - Shadows: `--shadow-sm`, `--shadow-md`

## ACCESSIBILITY

- Every `<input>` needs a visible or visually-hidden `<label>` with `htmlFor`.
- Every icon-only button needs `aria-label` describing its action and target (e.g. `Delete task 'Buy milk'`).
- Error messages: `role="alert"` so screen readers announce them immediately.
- Touch targets minimum 44×44 px via `min-width`/`min-height` in CSS.

## TESTING (BACKEND)

- Group tests in classes: `TestListTodos`, `TestCreateTodo`, etc.
- Each test docstring cites the FR number or Story AC it covers.
- Use the `client` fixture from `conftest.py` — never instantiate `TestClient` directly.

## TESTING (E2E — PLAYWRIGHT)

- Locators must be semantic: `getByRole`, `getByLabel`, `getByText`. No CSS selectors.
- Every test begins from a clean DB: delete all todos via the REST API in `beforeEach`.
- `workers: 1` in `playwright.config.ts` — keep tests sequential to avoid DB race conditions.
